activityList.description: I woke up feeling pretty terrible this morning tired, back hurt, throat hurt. I shook it off in the next hour so I went for a run.
This was a good one. It feels like I’m starting to get somewhere. I’ve been running slower, more often, and feeling better.
Heart rate was at 140 after half mile. Over 160 with half mile to go. I need a slower start. Monitoring heart rate during the run is helpful.

57 degrees. Cloudy but nice to be out. I can’t remember the last time it was this nice. A red tail hawk flew over the trail. It was carrying some small animal. It landed on a branch to my right and turned to look down at me as I passed.
Wind 24 mph. That was not the route to run.
Not feeling very good but it’s too nice outside.
